Description: Fragment of flattened handle of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora, gradual curve. Clay near fine pink-brown; cream slip. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Petrie Diary (EES Archive XVII 47) p. 55, 22 Name Ippokles. From same die as a pieve from Ephesos, Lawall, 2007. 34, AH8a.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0548)
